Overview  Service   Command 

Service: zimbraAccount
Namespace: "urn:zimbraAccount"
GetAvailableCsvFormats SOAP Command

Returns the known CSV formats that can be used for import and export of addressbook.

Authorization token required true
Admin Authorization token required false

GetAvailableCsvFormatsRequest

    <GetAvailableCsvFormatsRequest /> ## GetAvailableCsvFormatsRequest

GetAvailableCsvFormatsResponse

    <GetAvailableCsvFormatsResponse> ## GetAvailableCsvFormatsResponse
        (<csv [name="..."] /> ## NamedElement)*
    </GetAvailableCsvFormatsResponse>

The following table describes elements and attributes you can define within a <GetAvailableCsvFormatsResponse> element:

XPath Required / Optional Description
/csv Optional (0 or more) The known CSV formats that can be used for import and export of addressbook.
/csv@name Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
